FACTORS AFFECTING MEDIUM TERM LOAD FORECASTING:

1. Time(months, years)
2. Geological/Area (Population,type: residential ,commercial, industrial)
3. Living  Habits of people of targeted area
4. Weather (maximum and minimum monthly temperature at peak hours, speed of wind, clouds covering, barometric pressure,precipitation,solar irradiance along with humidity)
5. Socio-Economic Factors (GDP etc)
6. Electricity Price
7. Random Disturbances


